In a large saucepan over high heat, combine the water, curry powder, garlic, ginger, salt and onion. Bring to a boil, remove from heat and stir in rice. Cover and set aside to cool. In a large bowl, combine the turkey, apple, celery, bell pepper, green onion and raisins. Stir together, then stir in cooled rice mixture. To Make Vinaigrette: In a small bowl, whisk together the balsamic vinegar, red wine vinegar, oil, mustard, honey, garlic, salt and pepper. Toss salad with vinaigrette, and cover and refrigerate for 30 to 40 minutes or until well chilled. To Serve: Spoon some of the salad mixture onto each lettuce leaf and top with shredded coconut and peanuts.